<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10078c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10078c">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10078c"> 78(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> d = a (4th later letter) / Caesar&apos;s code</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Entour&eacute; de secr&eacute;taires, il <font color="green">[C&eacute;sar]</font> dicte &agrave; la fois quatre ou cinq lettres diff&eacute;rentes. Souvent il se sert d&apos;un <mark>chiffre</mark> dont la clef est indispensable pour le comprendre: ordinairement, il employait <mark>la quatri&egrave;me lettre apr&egrave;s celle dont il aurait d&ucirc; se servir</mark> dans l&apos;usage ordinaire. <font color="green">[Surrounded by secretaries, he [Caesar]</font> dictated four or five different letters at the same time. Often he uses a code whose key is indispensable for its comprehension: typically he used the fourth letter after the one he should have used in everyday speech.] <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 49</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
